# The `BasicTTIImpl.h` File Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

<Link id="l00242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="242"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instructioncost">InstructionCost</a> ConditionalCost = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="243"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (VariableMask) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Compute the cost of conditionally executing the memory operations with</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// variable masks. This includes extracting the individual conditions, a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// branches and PHIs to combine the results.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// NOTE: Estimating the cost of conditionally executing the memory</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// operations accurately is quite difficult and the current solution</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="259"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00260" /><CodeLine lineNumber="260"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00261" /><CodeLine lineNumber="261"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Checks if the provided mask \\p is a splat mask, i.e. it contains only -1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00262" /><CodeLine lineNumber="262"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// or same non -1 index value and this index value contained at least twice.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00263" /><CodeLine lineNumber="263"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// So, mask &lt;0, -1,-1, -1&gt; is not considered splat (it is just identity),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00264" /><CodeLine lineNumber="264"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// same for &lt;-1, 0, -1, -1&gt; (just a slide), while &lt;2, -1, 2, -1&gt; is a splat</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00265" /><CodeLine lineNumber="265"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// with \\p Index=2.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00266" /><CodeLine lineNumber="266"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> isSplatMask(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef&lt;int&gt;</a> Mask, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NumSrcElts, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">int</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;Index) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00267" /><CodeLine lineNumber="267"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Check that the broadcast index meets at least twice.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00268" /><CodeLine lineNumber="268"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> IsCompared = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00273" /><CodeLine lineNumber="273"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static&#95;cast&lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">&gt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/option/option-cpp/#a04665169063c8ca1f2ea96c27fc7c2b2">P</a>.value()) &gt;= NumSrcElts &#42; 2)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00274" /><CodeLine lineNumber="274"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00275" /><CodeLine lineNumber="275"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (SplatIdx == <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a9965a6249be879ba3d336a75a4f3efa7">PoisonMaskElem</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00276" /><CodeLine lineNumber="276"><span class="doxyHighlight">            SplatIdx = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/option/option-cpp/#a04665169063c8ca1f2ea96c27fc7c2b2">P</a>.value();</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="280"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> SplatIdx == <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/option/option-cpp/#a04665169063c8ca1f2ea96c27fc7c2b2">P</a>.value();</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><span class="doxyHighlight">                               <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/targettransforminfo/unrollingpreferences">TTI::UnrollingPreferences</a> &amp;UP,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><span class="doxyHighlight">                               <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/optimizationremarkemitter">OptimizationRemarkEmitter</a> &#42;ORE) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This unrolling functionality is target independent, but to provide some</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// motivation for its intended use, for x86:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00627" /><CodeLine lineNumber="627"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// According to the Intel 64 and IA-32 Architectures Optimization Reference</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Manual, Intel Core models and later have a loop stream detector (and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// associated uop queue) that can benefit from partial unrolling.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The relevant requirements are:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  - The loop must have no more than 4 (8 for Nehalem and later) branches</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    taken, and none of them may be calls.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  - The loop can have no more than 18 (28 for Nehalem and later) uops.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// According to the Software Optimization Guide for AMD Family 15h</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Processors, models 30h-4fh (Steamroller and later) have a loop predictor</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and loop buffer which can benefit from partial unrolling.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The relevant requirements are:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00640" /><CodeLine lineNumber="640"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  - The loop must have fewer than 16 branches</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00641" /><CodeLine lineNumber="641"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  - The loop must have less than 40 uops in all executed loop branches</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00642" /><CodeLine lineNumber="642"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00643" /><CodeLine lineNumber="643"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The number of taken branches in a loop is hard to estimate here, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00644" /><CodeLine lineNumber="644"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// benchmarking has revealed that it is better not to be conservative when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00645" /><CodeLine lineNumber="645"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// estimating the branch count. As a result, we&#39;ll ignore the branch limits</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00646" /><CodeLine lineNumber="646"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// until someone finds a case where it matters in practice.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00647" /><CodeLine lineNumber="647"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00648" /><CodeLine lineNumber="648"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MaxOps;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00649" /><CodeLine lineNumber="649"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetsubtargetinfo">TargetSubtargetInfo</a> &#42;ST = getST();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#af8107d78f45319b8c8c1505bc0d995bf">PartialUnrollingThreshold</a>.getNumOccurrences() &gt; 0)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00651" /><CodeLine lineNumber="651"><span class="doxyHighlight">      MaxOps = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#af8107d78f45319b8c8c1505bc0d995bf">PartialUnrollingThreshold</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00652" /><CodeLine lineNumber="652"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (ST-&gt;getSchedModel().LoopMicroOpBufferSize &gt; 0)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00653" /><CodeLine lineNumber="653"><span class="doxyHighlight">      MaxOps = ST-&gt;getSchedModel().LoopMicroOpBufferSize;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00654" /><CodeLine lineNumber="654"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00655" /><CodeLine lineNumber="655"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00656" /><CodeLine lineNumber="656"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Scan the loop: don&#39;t unroll loops with calls.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00658" /><CodeLine lineNumber="658"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> &#42;BB : L-&gt;blocks()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01510" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1510"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// sizes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01511" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1511"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mvt">MVT</a> VecTyLT = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicttiimplbase/#ab192bc3b4b8ccaa71341acf20e6ac335">getTypeLegalizationCost</a>(VecTy).second;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01512" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1512"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> VecTySize = thisT()-&gt;getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(VecTy);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01513" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1513"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> VecTyLTSize = VecTyLT.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mvt/#ab8e1af73424a59a00656c9ffd505c03f">getStoreSize</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01514" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1514"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01515" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1515"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Scale the cost of the memory operation by the fraction of legalized</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01516" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1516"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instructions that will actually be used. We shouldn&#39;t account for the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01517" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1517"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// cost of dead instructions since they will be removed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01518" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1518"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01519" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1519"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// E.g., An interleaved load of factor 8:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01520" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1520"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       %vec = load &lt;16 x i64&gt;, &lt;16 x i64&gt;&#42; %ptr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01521" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1521"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       %v0 = shufflevector %vec, undef, &lt;0, 8&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01522" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1522"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01523" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1523"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If &lt;16 x i64&gt; is legalized to 8 v2i64 loads, only 2 of the loads will be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01524" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1524"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// used (those corresponding to elements &#91;0:1&#93; and &#91;8:9&#93; of the unlegalized</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01525" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1525"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// type). The other loads are unused.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01526" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1526"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01527" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1527"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// TODO: Note that legalization can turn masked loads/stores into unmasked</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01528" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1528"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (legalized) loads/stores. This can be reflected in the cost.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01529" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1529"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a19921a3ceb99548f498d3df118eda9ed">Cost</a>.isValid() &amp;&amp; VecTySize &gt; VecTyLTSize) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01530" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1530"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The number of loads of a legal type it will take to represent a load</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01531" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1531"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of the unlegalized vector type.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01532" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1532"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NumLegalInsts = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a9dda4472ee0b7ea92ab49eedf6e13d50">divideCeil</a>(VecTySize, VecTyLTSize);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01533" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1533"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01534" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1534"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The number of elements of the unlegalized type that correspond to a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01535" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1535"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// single legal instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01536" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1536"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NumEltsPerLegalInst = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a9dda4472ee0b7ea92ab49eedf6e13d50">divideCeil</a>(NumElts, NumLegalInsts);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01537" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1537"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01538" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1538"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Determine which legal instructions will be used.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01539" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1539"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitvector">BitVector</a> UsedInsts(NumLegalInsts, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01540" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1540"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Index : Indices)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01541" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1541"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Elt = 0; Elt &lt; NumSubElts; ++Elt)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01542" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1542"><span class="doxyHighlight">          UsedInsts.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitvector/#a62237ebe27691377a942abe7446332ec">set</a>((Index + Elt &#42; Factor) / NumEltsPerLegalInst);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01543" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1543"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01544" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1544"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Scale the cost of the load by the fraction of legal instructions that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1545"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// will be used.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01546" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1546"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a19921a3ceb99548f498d3df118eda9ed">Cost</a> = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a9dda4472ee0b7ea92ab49eedf6e13d50">divideCeil</a>(UsedInsts.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitvector/#a568ff706b8c5991bd299c8c00b803897">count</a>() &#42; &#42;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a19921a3ceb99548f498d3df118eda9ed">Cost</a>.getValue(), NumLegalInsts);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01547" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1547"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01567" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1567"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// E.g. An interleaved load of factor 2 (with one member of index 0):</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1577"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                                </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;Insert&#42;/</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1581"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// insert them into the wide vector.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1582"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1583"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// E.g. An interleaved store of factor 3 with 2 members at indices 0,1:</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1587"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  true, true, false, true, true, false&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1588"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    call llvm.masked.store &lt;12 x i32&gt; %v0&#95;v1, &lt;12 x i32&gt;&#42; %ptr,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2718"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Try to calculate arithmetic and shuffle op costs for reduction intrinsics.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2719"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// We&#39;re assuming that reduction operation are performing the following way:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2720"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02721" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2721"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// %val1 = shufflevector&lt;n x t&gt; %val, &lt;n x t&gt; %undef,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2722"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// &lt;n x i32&gt; &lt;i32 n/2, i32 n/2 + 1, ..., i32 n, i32 undef, ..., i32 undef&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2723"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///            \\----------------v-------------/  \\----------v------------/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2724"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///                            n/2 elements               n/2 elements</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2725"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// %red1 = op &lt;n x t&gt; %val, &lt;n x t&gt; val1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02726" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2726"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// After this operation we have a vector %red1 where only the first n/2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2727"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// elements are meaningful, the second n/2 elements are undefined and can be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2728"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// dropped. All other operations are actually working with the vector of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2729"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// length n/2, not n, though the real vector length is still n.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2730"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// %val2 = shufflevector&lt;n x t&gt; %red1, &lt;n x t&gt; %undef,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02731" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2731"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// &lt;n x i32&gt; &lt;i32 n/4, i32 n/4 + 1, ..., i32 n/2, i32 undef, ..., i32 undef&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2732"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///            \\----------------v-------------/  \\----------v------------/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2733"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///                            n/4 elements               3&#42;n/4 elements</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2734"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// %red2 = op &lt;n x t&gt; %red1, &lt;n x t&gt; val2  - working with the vector of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2735"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// length n/2, the resulting vector has length n/4 etc.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2736"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2737"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The cost model should take into account that the actual length of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2738"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// vector is reduced on each iteration.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2739" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicttiimplbase/#a2c1b9368972e15e3602d4279f9988584"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instructioncost">InstructionCost</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicttiimplbase/#a2c1b9368972e15e3602d4279f9988584">getTreeReductionCost</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Opcode, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vectortype">VectorType</a> &#42;Ty,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2741"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Targets must implement a default value for the scalable case, since</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02799" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2799"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Try to calculate the cost of performing strict (in-order) reductions,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02800" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2800"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// which involves doing a sequence of floating point additions in lane</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02801" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2801"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// order, starting with an initial value. For example, consider a scalar</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02802" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2802"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// initial value &#39;InitVal&#39; of type float and a vector of type &lt;4 x float&gt;:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02803" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2803"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02804" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2804"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   Vector = &lt;float %v0, float %v1, float %v2, float %v3&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02805" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2805"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02806" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2806"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   %add1 = %InitVal + %v0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02807" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2807"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   %add2 = %add1 + %v1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02808" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2808"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   %add3 = %add2 + %v2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02809" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2809"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   %add4 = %add3 + %v3</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02810" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2810"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02811" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2811"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// As a simple estimate we can say the cost of such a reduction is 4 times</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02812" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2812"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the cost of a scalar FP addition. We can only estimate the costs for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02813" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2813"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// fixed-width vectors here because for scalable vectors we do not know the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02814" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2814"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// runtime number of operations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02815" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2815" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicttiimplbase/#a22615a6ebaa0232be4b70be555bf0690"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instructioncost">InstructionCost</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicttiimplbase/#a22615a6ebaa0232be4b70be555bf0690">getOrderedReductionCost</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Opcode, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vectortype">VectorType</a> &#42;Ty,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02816" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2816"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                          <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targettransforminfo/#a706f223f760b55668fbae74202b816bb">TTI::TargetCostKind</a> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/costmodel-cpp/#a162d8b2b3865594d1e14d828d2b8336a">CostKind</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02817" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2817"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Targets must implement a default value for the scalable case, since</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02818" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2818"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// we don&#39;t know how many lanes the vector has.</span></CodeLine>
